We considered that adaptive capacity was not differentiated by sector, and evaluated each country’s future adaptive capacity using the average per capita GDP for the years 2090–2100 using GDP and population projections (
 
  45
 ). We used the intermediate development scenario for the purpose of comparability between RCP scenarios. In countries where projected GDP per capita was not available (mostly small island nations), we used the gridded (0.5°) population and GDP version developed in (
 
  46
 ) based on data from (
 
  45
 ).
